@node "intro" "Introduction to this door..."

INTRODUCTION

This is a little door to view the stats :))
It shows :

* Almost all stats (BBS stats,Personal Stats,File Stats)

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements..."

REQUIREMENTS

* Amiga ;-)
* Kickstart 2.04+ / Workbench 2.0+
* RexxMast (running)
* Excelsior! v1.20+ 

Let's wait for Excelsior! v2.0 !! :))

@endnode
@node "install" "Installation"

INSTALLATION

Put this door WHERE EVER you want it....
You can put it in TEXT.WELCOME.USER.

Multiview/Amigaguide doesn't show the backslashes, so I have made
a snapshot of it, so it can't go wrong !
The snapshot is called TEXT.WELCOME.USER2.IFF it is also in
the archive !
You must add the line about File!stats11a.rexx !

You can also put it in the normal doors area...
Simply install it, it's an Arexx script, that should do it ;)

Or put in maybe in a textfile when the users enters the Filebase.
But maybe it gets irritating for the users if he sees it over
and over again ;)) (if he quits the filebase, and enters it more
then once)
The textfile command that shows itself when you enter the filebase
can be found in the Excelsior! Manual.

Anyway, I use it only in the login sequence...

@endnode
